    think='Now I have all the information I need to complete the review. Let me 
analyze each aspect:\n\n1. **全链路完整性**: This PR is a bug fix/improvement to
existing dev-tools feature. It only touches Mobile + Docs. No DB or API changes 
needed since this is a pure client-side bug fix. Since it\'s fixing existing UI 
behavior, it\'s reasonable that it doesn\'t include DB/API.\n\n2. **规范符合性**
: The code follows `docs/design-docs/flutter.md` well. The new pattern for BlocL
istener with listenWhen is actually documented in the PR\'s updates to flutter.m
d. SwTextField follows design system conventions.\n\n3. **契约一致性**: No share
d types changed. The PR only modifies Flutter mobile code.\n\n4. **测试覆盖**: T
he PR adds both unit tests (cubit) and widget tests. Good coverage for the bug b
eing fixed.\n\n5. **文档同步**: \n   - `docs/design-docs/flutter.md` is updated 
with the new best practice pattern\n   - `docs/modules/dev-tools.md` is updated\
n   - The module is already registered in `docs/modules/INDEX.md`\n   - No API d
ocs need updating since no API changed\n   - make check-docs passes\n\n6. **可运
行性**: make test and make lint fail due to missing dependencies (jest/eslint no
t installed), not code issues. make check-docs passes.\n\n7. **UI/设计一致性**: 
This is a **bug fix PR** - it fixes input reset, cursor jumping, and copy-paste 
issues in the existing ServerUrlTool. It doesn\'t introduce new UI design or cha
nge page structure/交互流程. According to the exception rules, "设计资产存在性" 
should be N/A. \n\nHowever, I should still check if there are any inconsistencie
s with the existing design spec (issue-29). The design spec exists, so I can do 
a quick check:\n- Colors: Uses DesignTokens.primary, DesignTokens.background, De
signTokens.textPrimary, DesignTokens.error - ✓\n- Font sizes: DesignTokens.fontS
izeBody for labels - ✓\n- Spacing: DesignTokens.spacingXs, spacingSm, spacingMd 
- ✓\n- SwTextField, SwButton, SwCard used correctly - ✓\n- The only visual chang
e is adding `enableInteractiveSelection: true` to SwTextField, which is a bug fi
x for copy-paste functionality and doesn\'t violate any design spec.\n\nLet me t
hink about any issues:\n\n1. The `_ServerUrlToolDemo` in widgetbook doesn\'t use
the new `FocusNode` pattern or `focusNode` prop on SwTextField. But since it\'s 
a demo/skeleton for visual review and doesn\'t use a real Cubit, this is probabl
y fine. However, it might be good practice to keep it consistent.\n\n2. In `dev_
tools_repository_impl.dart`, checking `prefs.setString()` return value: `SharedP
references.setString` on Android/iOS typically returns `Future<bool>`, but in so
me implementations or mock environments it might return `Future<void>`. The code
now checks `success` boolean. Looking at the `shared_preferences` package API, `
setString` does return `Future<bool>` in the standard implementation. This is a 
good defensive addition.\n\n3. In `dev_tools_cubit.dart`, `load()` now only sets
URL if `state.serverBaseUrl.isEmpty`. This prevents overwriting user input. Good
.\n\n4. In `server_url_tool.dart`, the `BlocListener` uses a `listenWhen` guard 
to only set controller text when:\n   - previous url was empty\n   - current url
is not empty\n   - controller text is empty\n   - focus node doesn\'t have focus
\n   \n   Wait, there\'s a subtle issue here. The `listenWhen` uses `_controller
.text.isEmpty && !_focusNode.hasFocus`. But what if the user typed something, th
en cleared it (so controller.text is empty), and then `load()` completes? In tha
t case, the listener would still overwrite the empty text with the loaded URL. B
ut since the user just cleared it, maybe they wanted it empty? However, given th
e default value is always a valid URL and empty is invalid, this edge case is pr
obably acceptable. The more important case is when the user has actually typed a
non-empty URL - that is protected.\n\nActually wait, looking more carefully at t
he listenWhen:\n```dart\nlistenWhen: (previous, current) =>\n    previous.server
BaseUrl.isEmpty &&\n    current.serverBaseUrl.isNotEmpty &&\n    _controller.tex
t.isEmpty &&\n    !_focusNode.hasFocus,\n```\n\nThis is correct for the initial 
load scenario. If the user clears the field (controller.text becomes empty), and
then load() emits a state change from empty to non-empty, it would reset. But in
practice, `load()` is typically called once at initialization, and the user hasn
\'t had time to clear and then have load() complete in a way that creates this t
ransition. The Cubit\'s `load()` method itself has a guard: `if (state.serverBas
eUrl.isEmpty) { emit(...) }`. So if the user already typed something and `onUrlC
hanged(\'\')` was emitted, `state.serverBaseUrl` is empty. Then when `load()` is
called again and gets the default URL, `previous.serverBaseUrl` is empty and `cu
rrent.serverBaseUrl` is not empty. If `controller.text` is also empty (user clea
red it), the listener would fire. This is a corner case but given the design con
text (default URL should always be shown rather than empty), it\'s reasonable.\n
\n5. The SwTextField now has `enableInteractiveSelection: true` added. This is a
ctually the default for TextField, so explicitly adding it is fine and documents
intent.\n\nLet me think about any real issues:\n\n- **Widgetbook demo doesn\'t u
se `focusNode`**: The `_ServerUrlToolDemo` in widgetbook doesn\'t pass `focusNod
e` to `SwTextField`. Since this is just a visual demo without real Cubit/BlocLis
tener, it doesn\'t need it. But it might be nice to be consistent. Not a blockin
g issue.\n\n- **No BDD tests modified**: This is a bug fix to existing behavior,
and the BDD feature file already describes the expected behavior. No change need
ed.\n\n- **Golden files**: The docs mention `apps/mobile/test/goldens/dev_tools_
drawer_default.png` and `server_url_tool_error.png` should exist. Let me check i
f they exist.\n\nActually wait, I should check whether golden files exist, since
the PR is a UI change.',
